init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You order the bee to get off you, and it does so.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There is a long pause as you try to think of something to say.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you ask her to leave, will they all leave you alone?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: What do you say to her?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm sorry, Your Majesty, I can't move to Minnesota.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Then I order you to go there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You have a feeling that she's going to follow through on her promise, and you feel satisfied.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You've never felt better in your life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As the sun sets, you make your way back home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You reach into your pants pocket to get your keys, and your hand hits something weird.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: unlock your bicycle, and sit down.
